//*
//* [WEATHERAB 0] 	//The weather definition ID. Referenced from regions.dfn as ABWEATH=...
//*  COLDCHANCE # 	//This is the chance of there being a cold snap on the day.
//*               	//If it passes, then there will be a modification of the MINTEMP
//*               	//to be lower, based on the fact it's colder.
//*  COLDINTENSITY # 	//Currently unused
//*  HEATCHANCE # 	//Chance of there being a heat wave on the day. If it passes, then there
//*			//will be a modification of MAXTEMP to be higher, based on it being a heat wave.
//*  HEATINTENSITY # 	//Currently unused
//*  LIGHTMIN # 	//Minimum light level of the day (midnight).
//*  LIGHTMAX # 	//Maximum light level of the day (noon).
//*  MAXTEMP #		//Maximum temperature of the day. Can be affected by heat waves.
//*			//Above 20 degrees, Krrios' client takes on an orange tinge.
//*  MINTEMP #		//Minimum temperature of the day. Can be affected by cold snaps.
//*			//Below 10 degrees, Krrios' client takes on a blue tinge.
//*  MAXWIND #		//Currently unused.
//*  MINWIND #		//Currently unused.
//*  RAINCHANCE #	//Chance of there being rain on the day(only if snowchance fails to snow).
//*  RAININTENSITY #	//Currently unused.
//*  SNOWCHANCE #	//Chance of there being snow on the day.  Will override rainchance.
//*  SNOWINTENSITY #	//Currently unused.
//*  SNOWTHRESHOLD #    //The temperature at which snow will STOP. So if it's 15, then when
//*			//the region hits 15 degrees or above, it won't snow (but it might rain)
//*****************************************************************

